INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'a82ca3b3-d37c-4973-beee-d37aa1c02143',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$HuggingFace TextStreamer — Token-by-Token Output Without the Wait$escape$,
  $escape$HuggingFace's `TextStreamer` and `TextIteratorStreamer` give you two distinct streaming patterns. `TextStreamer` prints tokens to stdout as they're generated — zero effort, great for CLI tools. `TextIteratorStreamer` is the real workhorse: it runs generation in a background thread and exposes a Python iterator, letting your main thread consume tokens and push them to a UI, WebSocket, or SSE endpoint.

The key gotcha: generation must run in a separate thread. If you call `model.generate()` on the main thread with `TextIteratorStreamer`, it blocks until completion — defeating the purpose entirely.

Pass `skip_prompt=True` to suppress the echoed input tokens, and `skip_special_tokens=True` to strip `<|end|>` artifacts from the stream. For chat models, combine with `tokenizer.apply_chat_template()` before streaming to handle the system/user turn structure correctly.

For web APIs, wrap the iterator in a FastAPI `StreamingResponse` with `media_type="text/event-stream"`. Each yielded token chunk becomes an SSE frame — the frontend receives progressive output with no polling.$escape$,
  $escape$from transformers import AutoTokenizer, AutoModelForCausalLM, TextIteratorStreamer
from threading import Thread

tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained("mistralai/Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.2")
model = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained("mistralai/Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.2", device_map="auto")

inputs = tokenizer(["Explain attention mechanisms:"], return_tensors="pt").to(model.device)
streamer = TextIteratorStreamer(tokenizer, skip_prompt=True, skip_special_tokens=True)

thread = Thread(target=model.generate, kwargs={**inputs, "streamer": streamer, "max_new_tokens": 200})
thread.start()

for token in streamer:
    print(token, end="", flush=True)$escape$,
  $escape$python$escape$,
